{"questionId":"33097953","questionHtml":"<p>In the case that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mtext>OP</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover></math>&nbsp;is perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover></math>, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mtext>OP</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>·</mo><mover><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; (may be seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to multiply out scalar product&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">&nbsp;</mo><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">&nbsp;</mo><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute for&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></math> &nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi></mfenced></math> &nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>λ</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi><mo>·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></mrow><mrow><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">a</mi></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">b</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use cosine rule to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to apply Pythagoras’ Theorem twice:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>O</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>O</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve simultaneously:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>λ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33097953","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"In the case that OP→ is perpendicular to AB→, find the value of λ.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector definitions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}